    • Constructor Detail

      • TAG_FLAC_PICTURE

        public TAG_FLAC_PICTURE()
        Create an object that holds a null TAG_FLAC_PICTURE.
        The call isNull() on the object created will returns true.
          TAG_FLAC_PICTURE obj = new TAG_FLAC_PICTURE();
  (obj == null) <=> false
  obj.isNull() <=> true
        To creates a new TAG_FLAC_PICTURE, use the static "constructor" : 
          TAG_FLAC_PICTURE obj = TAG_FLAC_PICTURE.allocate();
        See Also:
        allocate()

    • Method Detail

      • asTAG_FLAC_PICTURE

        public static TAG_FLAC_PICTURE asTAG_FLAC_PICTURE(Pointer pointer)
        Create a view of the Pointer object as a TAG_FLAC_PICTURE object.
        This view is valid only if the memory holded by the Pointer holds a TAG_FLAC_PICTURE object.
